Mass Funeral for the R617 Kilmun Road Crash victims at Kilmun Sportground in Bulwer KwaZulu-Natal BULWER - Thirteen members of the Mndali family have been laid to rest in Bulwer, in the KwaZulu-Natal Midlands.
All 13 people died last Saturday when the taxi they were travelling in rolled down an embankment near Underberg. They had been returning from a ceremony. READ: Mbalula conveys condolences after deadly KZN crash A two-year toddler was among those killed. KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala attended the funeral and was accompanied by Transport MEC Bheki Ntuli. Ntuli addressed mourners and says his department is committed to ending carnage on the province's roads.